<section class="block-section story">
  <span class="section-tag">📖 Story</span>
  <h2>Why this block matters</h2>
  <p class="sub">The move that makes this class different from most.</p>
  <p>AI outputs are sources. Same OPVL framework, same critical eye. Today we make that move explicit by running OPVL on an <strong>AI summary of the same anchor article you OPVL'd yesterday</strong> — the <a href="/units/unit-0/block-2/">[U0 Anchor Article — TBD pending librarian]</a>. Same content, different source type. The Origin / Purpose / Value / Limitation outputs will diverge. That divergence <em>is</em> the lesson. Then we introduce the habit you'll carry for the rest of the year: <strong>every time you use AI in your work, you fill out the AI Documentation Template</strong>.</p>
  <p>The documentation isn't there to police you. It's there to make you notice what the AI did versus what you did. Students who can articulate that distinction learn more from AI than students who can't. Honest disclosure = no penalty. Hidden AI use = academic integrity violation. That's the whole protocol.</p>
</section>

