<section class="block-section do">
  <span class="section-tag">🛠️ Do</span>
  <h2>Today's work — choose one path</h2>
  <p class="sub">All four options end the same way: a completed AI Documentation Template. The path you pick changes what AI you use and what question you ask.</p>
  <div class="choice-intro">
    <strong>Learning Intention:</strong> I can use an AI on a low-stakes question and produce a complete, specific AI Documentation Template — including at least one specific thing the AI got wrong.
  </div>
  <div class="choice-board">
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">A</div>
      <div class="choice-title">AI summary of the anchor article (default)</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">Ask Gemini (free through AISC Workspace) to summarise the <strong>[U0 Anchor Article — TBD pending librarian]</strong>. Save the conversation. OPVL the AI response. Fill out the full AI Documentation Template. Compare to your Block 2 OPVL of the original article — what specifically differs in your Limitation entry?</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Solo · Default</span>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">B</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Compare two AIs on the same anchor article (stretch)</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">Ask both Gemini and Claude to summarise the anchor article. OPVL each response separately. Where do they disagree? Whose Limitations matter more? Document both in your AI Documentation Template.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Solo · Stretch</span>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">C</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Push back with The Skeptic (practice)</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">Ask The Skeptic AI partner to challenge the anchor article's main argument. Notice what it questions in the article and in the AI summary. Document the back-and-forth.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Solo · Practice</span>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">D</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Pick your own low-stakes topic (choice)</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">If you went Path C in Block 2 (student-found article), continue that thread today — ask AI about your own source rather than the anchor article. Same full AI Documentation Template. Bring your "one thing it got wrong" to the table share.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Solo · Choice</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

